                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.113/278: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harvey</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="71" xml:id="d506fn71">See last paragraph for instructions
                        to repeat to Paris, Brussels, The Hague, and Lisbon. A similar telegram,
                        with the omission of the last paragraph, was sent to the Ambassador in Japan
                        as no. 68.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-06-29T15:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 29, 1922—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>188. Department’s 157, June 2, 3 p.m.</p>
                <p>The Italian Government has now indicated its approval of the proposal of this
                    Government to obtain from the Governments which participated in the Conference
                    on Limitation of Armament the adoption of the amended resolution covering
                    shipments of arms and munitions of war to China. You will so inform the
                    Government to which you are accredited requesting it in view of its favorable
                    attitude announced at the time of the Conference, to indicate to this Government
                    through you its formal approval of the amended resolution which reads as
                    follows:—</p>
                <p>[Here follows text of resolution quoted in telegram no. 157, June 2, to the
                    Ambassador in Great Britain, printed on <ref target="#pg_729">page
                    729</ref>.]</p>
                <p>Repeat to Paris, Brussels, The Hague and Lisbon.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
